    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long, straight-bladed swords with a grip long enough to allow them to be grasped by one hand plus two or three fingers of the other, used in the 15th and 16th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
